         <div id="section">Week 1: Nonlinear Equations</div>
         <div>
	   Find the root of the nonlinear Euler Equation:
	   $$R_f = \frac{1}{\beta} \left(\frac{c_{t+1}}{c_t}\right)^{\gamma},$$
	   where \(\beta=0.99\), \(R_f = 1.04\) and \(\gamma=1.1\). Further, assume that
	   $$c_{t+1} = \alpha_0 + \alpha_1 c_t,$$
	   where \(\alpha_0 = 0.01\) and \(\alpha_1 = 1.02\). Find the root using the
	   bisection method, function iteration, Newton's method and Broyden's method.
	   <iframe width='100%' height='300' src='http://www.r-fiddle.org/#/embed?id=xhJImm9e&version=5' allowfullscreen='allowfullscreen' frameborder='0'></iframe>
